// Breakout level 1 — the classic 6x10 rainbow brick grid.
//
// Only bricks live in this scene; walls, paddle, ball, and sensors are
// code-spawned (their colors are chaos-theme-driven at runtime). The game
// re-instantiates this scene on every match start.
//
// Conventions the game relies on:
// - Entity names follow "brick_r{row}_c{col}" — the row digit drives the
//   score payout (see levels::brick_row_from_name), so keep names intact
//   when editing. Bricks without a parseable row still score the minimum.
// - Collider half-extents are absolute pixels; sprite size comes from
//   Transform2D scale x 80 (RENDER_UNIT). Keep them in sync: scale =
//   (width/80, height/80) for a (width/2, height/2) collider.
// - The "BrickRow*" prefabs are authoring sugar only — the editor's save
//   pipeline flattens prefabs into inline components, and the game does
//   not depend on them.
SceneData(
    name: "Breakout Level 1",
    prefabs: {
        // Row 0: red
        "BrickRow0": PrefabData(
            components: [
                Transform2D(scale: (0.875, 0.3)),
